Hey, sonny.

11:01.430 --> 11:03.599
- Hello.
- What's the matter?

11:03.766 --> 11:05.142
Nothing. Why?

11:05.309 --> 11:07.311
It's late at night,
where are you going?

11:07.478 --> 11:10.272
- To join the Navy.
- Oh, well, you...

11:10.439 --> 11:14.652
- Gonna what?
- I said, I'm going to join the Navy.

11:17.321 --> 11:19.198
- Wait a minute.
- I'm in a hurry.

11:19.365 --> 11:21.992
Take it easy. Where do you live?

11:22.159 --> 11:24.161
- Why?
- Well, I wanna take you home.

11:24.745 --> 11:28.457
But I'm not going home.
I've just come from there.

11:29.291 --> 11:31.168
What's your name?

11:33.462 --> 11:35.965
Look, it's my job
to find little boys that are lost.

11:36.131 --> 11:38.342
Lost is when you don't know
where you're going.

11:38.509 --> 11:41.553
And I do know,
I'm going to join the Navy.

11:41.762 --> 11:43.138
- All right.
- Good night.

11:43.305 --> 11:46.475
If that's the way you want it, okay.
You're coming to the station.

11:46.642 --> 11:49.687
I don't wanna join the police.
I wanna join the Navy.

12:56.962 --> 12:58.797
Stop there.

13:01.634 --> 13:04.219
Are you following me?

13:10.851 --> 13:12.436
What's with you?

13:12.603 --> 13:14.188
Come on, spill it.

13:14.355 --> 13:16.440
Well, you see, it's like this, Joe.

13:16.607 --> 13:18.567
I've been in the Navy
a year and a half.

13:18.734 --> 13:20.903
Every time we hit port and get liberty

13:21.070 --> 13:23.530
all I do is go to the library.

13:23.697 --> 13:26.033
All right, so you like books,
what's the beef?

13:26.200 --> 13:29.411
Well, I thought it'd be fun
to try something different

13:29.578 --> 13:31.246
like going out with girls.

13:31.413 --> 13:34.166
- Okay, good luck.
- But I don't know how to begin.

13:34.333 --> 13:36.627
Oh, no, wait a minute.
Don't give me that "but."

13:36.794 --> 13:39.797
After all, you're no yokel.
You're from Brooklyn.

13:40.005 --> 13:42.800
Even in Brooklyn, things can go wrong.

13:42.967 --> 13:44.426
What do you mean?

13:44.593 --> 13:46.387
Well, right from boys' high school

13:46.553 --> 13:49.098
I went to the
Cathedral of Saint John the Divine

13:49.264 --> 13:51.308
assistant choirmaster.

13:51.600 --> 13:54.228
And out of there, I went into the Navy.

13:54.603 --> 13:56.897
I wouldn't tell that
to anyone but you, Joe.

13:57.106 --> 13:58.607
Sure, sure, I'll keep it quiet.

13:58.774 --> 14:00.859
What do you want,
a couple of phone numbers?

14:01.026 --> 14:03.237
Oh, no, I'd be too scared to use them.

14:03.404 --> 14:06.031
- When you mentioned Lola, I thought...
- Lola?

14:06.198 --> 14:07.533
- Yeah.
- Hey, are you kidding?

14:07.700 --> 14:09.034
Oh, not what you think, Joe.

14:09.201 --> 14:11.537
I thought I'd like
to string along and learn.

14:11.704 --> 14:14.873
After all, you're the best wolf
in the whole Navy.

14:15.040 --> 14:18.293
Well, you are.
And besides, you gotta help me, Joe.

14:18.460 --> 14:21.297
You saved my life
and you owe me something.

14:21.463 --> 14:25.384
I saved your life
so now I owe you something?

14:25.551 --> 14:27.094
Have you gone crazy?

14:27.261 --> 14:30.973
Look, I didn't ask you to save my life,
but you did.

14:31.140 --> 14:34.810
- Now I figure you're responsible for me.
- Well, I don't.

14:34.977 --> 14:39.231
What's the sense of having your life
saved if you can't have any fun with it?

14:43.485 --> 14:46.030
Look, I got a lot to do
in the next four days.

14:46.196 --> 14:47.740
I don't want anybody tailing me.

14:47.948 --> 14:49.658
You say I owe you something.

14:49.825 --> 14:52.995
Well, I don't see it,
but if I find a dame for you

14:53.162 --> 14:55.497
and get you started,
will you call it quits?

14:57.791 --> 15:01.003
Okay, let me see.

15:07.843 --> 15:09.928
Well, we'll have to do
with what you've got.

15:10.471 --> 15:12.556
First place, fix your hat.

15:18.228 --> 15:20.064
Let me see a sample of your technique.

15:20.230 --> 15:22.983
You're you, see?
And I'm a dame coming down the street.

15:23.150 --> 15:24.860
Pick me up.

15:26.487 --> 15:29.782
I'm a dame, see? I'm coming down
the street, now come on.

15:29.948 --> 15:32.409
I beg your pardon, miss.
Lady, could I possibly...?

15:32.576 --> 15:35.204
Oh, no. No.

15:35.412 --> 15:36.872
You gotta give it more:

15:55.641 --> 15:59.186
Listen, Brooklyn, when you're going
hunting it's how you feel that counts.

15:59.353 --> 16:02.064
If you feel like a mouse,
you'll be looking for cheese

16:02.231 --> 16:04.942
that's what you'll get.
But if you feel like a wolf

16:05.109 --> 16:07.111
nothing can go wrong,
you're in control.

16:07.277 --> 16:10.406
Hey, sailors, one of you guys gotta
come down to station with me.

16:10.572 --> 16:13.450
- Any choice? You'll do. Come on.
- Hey, wait a minute.

16:13.617 --> 16:15.619
Please, let's not have
any unpleasantness.

16:15.786 --> 16:18.706
I'll go with you, Joe.
How can this happen to me?

16:18.872 --> 16:21.625
Just when I'm beginning
to feel like a wolf.

16:23.127 --> 16:25.629
The secretary of the Navy
will have a say about this.

16:25.796 --> 16:27.256
Washington will hear about it.

16:27.423 --> 16:29.717
Who's in charge here?
That's what I wanna know.

16:29.883 --> 16:32.386
- Ship ahoy!
- Are you the guy that had me pulled in?

16:32.553 --> 16:35.764
- Pardon me for not getting up.
- What's the charge? What's the idea?

16:35.931 --> 16:38.309
- What are you...?
- If you've been inconvenienced

16:38.475 --> 16:39.810
I'm sorry.

16:39.977 --> 16:42.604
You see, this young man
thinks he should join the Navy.

16:42.771 --> 16:44.315
We think he should go home.

16:44.481 --> 16:47.276
Since he won't tell us where he lives

16:47.860 --> 16:49.862
we thought that maybe a sailor...

16:50.029 --> 16:51.572
See?

16:59.705 --> 17:01.373
So you wanna join the Navy, huh?

17:02.374 --> 17:03.709
Aye, aye, sir.

17:05.586 --> 17:07.421
Attention.

17:07.588 --> 17:09.589
- Name?
- Don Martin, sir.

17:09.757 --> 17:13.176
- Where do you live?
- 1515 Foothill Road.

17:20.142 --> 17:21.602
My daddy was in the Navy

17:21.769 --> 17:24.313
and he said that when
I was grown up, I could join.

17:24.521 --> 17:27.066
And now I am grown up, so I want to.

17:29.068 --> 17:32.029
Well, sure, mate, but...

17:32.196 --> 17:35.449
Well, look, it's this way.
There's sort of a rule in the Navy.

17:35.658 --> 17:40.496
Before they'll take you, you need a letter
from your mom or dad saying it's okay.

17:41.038 --> 17:43.624
But I don't have
a mother or father anymore.

17:46.001 --> 17:48.212
I live with my Aunt Susie.

17:48.420 --> 17:51.006
You think a letter from an aunt
would be all right?

17:51.215 --> 17:55.928
Well, sure, that would be perfect.
Why don't you talk to her about it.

17:56.095 --> 17:58.305
One of these guys
will take you home and...

17:58.472 --> 18:00.516
- You.
- But I got...

18:01.266 --> 18:05.229
- Gotta be a nursemaid and everything...
- Aunt Susie may not give me the letter

18:05.396 --> 18:07.690
but if you asked her...

18:07.856 --> 18:09.984
- You better come along too.
- Oh, no, I can't.

18:10.150 --> 18:11.610
- You come along.
- No, I can't.

18:11.777 --> 18:13.404
What am I gonna do about Lola?

18:18.325 --> 18:20.953
I guess Aunt Susie must be asleep, huh?

18:21.120 --> 18:23.956
- She isn't home yet.
- I suppose the door is locked too.

18:24.123 --> 18:25.582
Yes.

18:26.458 --> 18:28.460
- But we can get in.
- How?

18:28.627 --> 18:30.921
The way I got out.

18:38.637 --> 18:41.181
Look out for my wagon.

18:48.564 --> 18:51.650
"Dear Ms. Abbott,
Donald was a very good boy.

18:51.817 --> 18:54.111
He's fast asleep.

18:54.486 --> 18:57.323
So I went home. Mrs. Murphy."

18:57.948 --> 18:59.408
I'll get you some candy.

18:59.575 --> 19:02.036
- I know where Aunt Susie hides it.
- Wait a second.

19:02.202 --> 19:04.747
- You think your aunt will be back soon?
- Oh, sure.

19:04.913 --> 19:07.875
What do you mean, "oh, sure"?
How do you know?

19:08.042 --> 19:10.169
Well, she lives here.

19:11.587 --> 19:13.756
You know, sometimes he talks like you.

19:25.976 --> 19:27.561
Look, fellas...

19:27.728 --> 19:32.691
I don't want you to get the wrong idea.
I don't want you to think I'd walk out...

19:32.900 --> 19:36.737
Well, you gotta stay here with the kid
anyhow and talk to his aunt and...

19:36.945 --> 19:40.532
Well, I got a date with a girl,
and there's no sense in all of us just...

19:40.699 --> 19:44.453
Well, that's great. That's just dandy.

19:44.620 --> 19:48.165
He's got a date with a girl. What's he
think I've got a date with, a duck?

